title: Big Ten football | Iowa running back named offensive player of the week | Buckeye Xtra Sports
text:
Iowa running back Jordan Canzeri is the Big Ten's offensive player of the week, the conference announced this morning.
Canzeri, a senior, set a school record with 43 carries and had a career-high 256 rushing yards in a 29-20 victory over Illinois. In addition to the 75-yard TD run, Canzeri had two catches for 15 yards and a touchdown.
Other honorees this week:
Defense:  Jourdan Lewis, CB, Michigan
Special teams:  Jehu Chesson, Michigan
Freshmen of the week:  Jabrill Peppers, S, Michigan and Shannon Brooks, RB, Minnesota
